Had same problem here as @d10genes – the custom.js was being included, & top-level console message show, but the 'Binding' message and add_shortcut not run. (Using notebook 4.2.2; Chrome/52.)

But, stripping the file down to _not_ register-for-later-eventing fixed the problem. That is: 

```
$ cat .jupyter/custom/custom.js 
console.info('Binding Ctrl-J/K to move cell up/down');
Jupyter.keyboard_manager.command_shortcuts.add_shortcut('Ctrl-k','jupyter-notebook:move-cell-up');
Jupyter.keyboard_manager.command_shortcuts.add_shortcut('Ctrl-j','jupyter-notebook:move-cell-down');
```

Maybe now `custom.js` now only runs at the right event? 

If so, would be nice for jupyter/notebook#21 to be updated with a working recipe (@Carreau, @jhamrick).

